com.yworks.yfiles.graph.styles

Class ArcEdgeStyle

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.yworks.yfiles.graph.styles.ArcEdgeStyle
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IArrowOwner, IEdgeStyle, ICloneable, Cloneable

    public class ArcEdgeStyle
extends Object
implements IEdgeStyle, IArrowOwner, Cloneable
    Provides an arc representation for an edge.

    The rendering does not take into account bends of an edge, instead the arc's height is determined as a fixed ratio or fixed height.

    This style uses an ArcEdgeStyleRenderer for its visualization.

      • getHeight

        public final double getHeight()
        Gets the "height" of the arc.

        Depending on the setting of FixedHeightEnabled, this value is interpreted differently: If FixedHeightEnabled is disabled, the height of the arc will depend on it's width. The width will be multiplied by this value to obtain the height. If the FixedHeightEnabled feature is enabled, this value will be interpreted as the absolute height.

        The default value is 0.

        Returns:
        The height of the arc, either relative or absolute.
        See Also:
        setHeight(double)

        public final boolean isHeightHandleProviderEnabled()
